Memory Match Sidegame
=====================

A terminal-based memory matching game built with C++ and ncurses. Test your memory by matching pairs of symbols on a 4x4 grid!


Features
--------

- 4x4 grid with 8 unique symbol pairs
- 20 lives to complete the game
- Help feature (5 uses) - temporarily reveals all cards
- Color-coded interface (if terminal supports it)
- 5-second memorization phase at the start
- Full keyboard controls


Requirements
------------

- C++17 compatible compiler (g++, clang++)
- ncurses library
- Make build system


Installing ncurses
------------------

Ubuntu/Debian:
    sudo apt-get install libncurses-dev

Fedora/RHEL:
    sudo dnf install ncurses-devel

Arch Linux:
    sudo pacman -S ncurses

macOS:
    brew install ncurses


Compilation
-----------

Simply run:
    make

To clean build files:
    make clean


How to Run
----------

After compilation:
    ./memory


How to Play
-----------

Objective:
    Match all 8 pairs of symbols on a 4x4 grid before running out of lives.

Gameplay:
    1. Memorization Phase: All cards are revealed for 5 seconds at the start. 
       Use this time to memorize the positions!

    2. Main Game:
       - Cards start face-down (shown as ?)
       - Select a card with arrow keys and press ENTER or SPACE to reveal it
       - Select a second card to try and find a match
       - If symbols match: both cards stay revealed and you earn a pair
       - If symbols don't match: both cards flip back and you lose 1 life


Controls
--------

    Arrow Keys     - Move cursor
    ENTER / SPACE  - Select/reveal card
    H              - Use help (reveals all cards for 2 seconds)
    Q              - Quit game


Scoring
-------

    Starting lives : 20
    Match success  : +1 pair, no life change
    Match failure  : -1 life
    Help uses      : 5 maximum
    Win condition  : Match all 8 pairs
    Loss condition : Run out of lives (0 remaining)


